 @Target(value=TYPE)
public @interface API

      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      java.lang.String prefix

      boolean proxy
      If proxy is set to true, then all methods of the class are simplied proxied, where the first arg of each proxy call is either the the class type, or an object, and the fixed class type is resolved dynamically, using the resolver() value

    • Element Detail

      • group

        public abstract java.lang.String group

      • proxy

        public abstract boolean proxy
        If proxy is set to true, then all methods of the class are simplied proxied, where the first arg of each proxy call is either the the class type, or an object, and the fixed class type is resolved dynamically, using the resolver() value
        Returns:
        Default:
        false

      • resolver

        public abstract java.lang.String resolver
        Resolver is only used if the proxy=true. When a resolver is used, then a second method is created in the api that accepts an Object arg as the first arg. The method implementation will then use the resolver to resolve the object type and then proxy the call, if possible.
        Returns:
        Default:
        ""

      • prefix

        public abstract java.lang.String prefix
        Deprecated. - no longer used, but needed for awhile to build the api tranlation tool
        Prefix is used with proxy, to prefix all methods with this value. ie, if the prefix is "Show" and the method is getTitle, then the API method is GetShowTitle
        Returns:
        Default:
        ""
